== 起源 ==
'''Touchpress'''由[[Theodore_Gray|Theodore Gray]], Max Whitby, John Cromie和[[史蒂芬·沃爾夫勒姆|史蒂芬·沃爾夫勒姆]]在iPad发布后不久创立。<ref name="PubWeekly">{{cite news | url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/digital/content-and-e-books/article/48187-touchpress-theodore-gray-tests-his-mettle-in-the-app-world.html | title=TouchPress: Theodore Gray Tests His Mettle in the App World | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Roush, Wade | date=2011-07-29 | publisher=Publisher's Weekly | archive-date=2014-12-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141217031539/http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/digital/content-and-e-books/article/48187-touchpress-theodore-gray-tests-his-mettle-in-the-app-world.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="WolfBlog">{{cite news | url=http://blog.stephenwolfram.com/2010/12/touch-press-the-second-book/ | title=Touch Press: The Second Book | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Wolfram, Stephen | date=2010-12-24 | publisher=Stephen Wolfram Blog | archive-date=2013-09-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130914051907/http://blog.stephenwolfram.com/2010/12/touch-press-the-second-book/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>首个被出版的应用是“元素” ("The Elements")，创意来自于几位创始人在一张咖啡桌前共同讨论完成的一部关于元素周期表的书籍。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/technology/2010/04/the-curious-tale-of-the-wooden-table-that-became-an-ipad-book.html | title=The curious tale of the wooden table that became an iPad book | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Pham, Alex | date=2010-04-27 | publisher=The Los Angeles Times | archive-date=2014-12-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224180925/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/technology/2010/04/the-curious-tale-of-the-wooden-table-that-became-an-ipad-book.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 设计理念 ==
'''Touchpress'''创作“活书”。<ref name="Forbes">{{cite news | url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/tedgreenwald/2012/04/27/the-coffee-table-ebook-ipad-apps-from-touch-press-transform-the-act-of-reading/ | title=The Coffee Table eBook: iPad Apps From Touch Press Transform The Act Of Reading | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Ng, David | date=2012-04-27 | publisher=Forbes | archive-date=2014-12-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141208204123/http://www.forbes.com/sites/tedgreenwald/2012/04/27/the-coffee-table-ebook-ipad-apps-from-touch-press-transform-the-act-of-reading/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>他们的应用序具有许多互动元素，争取引起读者更深了解主题的兴趣。该公司是重新定义21世纪书籍和阅读体验这一广泛运动的一部分。<ref name="Xconomy">{{cite news | url=http://www.xconomy.com/national/2012/05/11/touch-press-the-ipad-and-the-new-golden-age-of-multimedia/ | title=Touch Press, the iPad, and the New Golden Age of Multimedia | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Roush, Wade | date=2012-05-11 | publisher=Xconomy | archive-date=2014-12-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210140223/http://www.xconomy.com/national/2012/05/11/touch-press-the-ipad-and-the-new-golden-age-of-multimedia/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="WSJ">{{cite news | url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052702303411604575167932497910828.html | title=For the iPad, Apps With Their Own Wow Factor | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Boehret, Katherine | date=2010-04-07 | publisher=The Wall Street Journal | archive-date=2011-12-30 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111230091445/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052702303411604575167932497910828.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>Touchpress尤其以其与出版业内外的伙伴合作而著名。迄今为止，该公司已与[[迪斯尼|迪斯尼]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.macrumors.com/2013/08/08/disney-animated-for-ipad-covers-the-history-of-all-53-disney-films/ | title='Disney Animated' for iPad Covers the History of All 53 Disney Films | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Padilla, Richard | date=2013-08-08 | publisher=Mac Rumors | archive-date=2014-12-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209023513/http://www.macrumors.com/2013/08/08/disney-animated-for-ipad-covers-the-history-of-all-53-disney-films/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[德意志唱片公司|德意志唱片公司]]，<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/tomserviceblog/2013/may/31/beethoven-ninth-symphony-app | title='Beethoven's Ninth, the app: an Ode to iJoy | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Service, Tom | date=2013-05-31 | publisher=The Guardian | archive-date=2014-12-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209010704/http://www.theguardian.com/music/tomserviceblog/2013/may/31/beethoven-ninth-symphony-app | dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[费伯和费伯公司|费伯和费伯公司]]，[[谢默斯·希尼|谢默斯·希尼]]<ref name="Waste Telegraph Review" />，[[比约克|比约克]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.wired.co.uk/magazine/archive/2011/08/features/music-nature-science/page/2 | title='In depth: How Björk's 'Biophilia' album fuses music with iPad apps | accessdate=August 13, 2013 | author=Burton, Charlie | date=2011-07-26 | publisher=Wired | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415091429/http://www.wired.co.uk/magazine/archive/2011/08/features/music-nature-science/page/2 | archivedate=2014-04-15 }}</ref>，[[费欧娜·萧|费欧娜·萧]]，[[帕特里克·斯图尔特|帕特里克·斯图尔特]]，[[史蒂芬·弗莱|史蒂芬·弗莱]]，[[安德鲁·莫申|安德鲁·莫申]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.appolicious.com/articles/12419-touch-press-brushes-the-dust-off-the-sonnets-by-shakespeare | title='Touch Press brushes the dust off The Sonnets by Shakespeare | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Caplan, Lisa | date=2012-12-14 | publisher=Appolicious | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209101045/http://www.appolicious.com/articles/12419-touch-press-brushes-the-dust-off-the-sonnets-by-shakespeare | archivedate=2014-12-09 }}</ref>，[[斯蒂芬·霍夫|斯蒂芬·霍夫]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.classicalsource.com/db_control/db_news.php?id=2497 | title=Stephen Hough And Touch Press Release Ground-Breaking iPad App Coinciding With Opening Concert Of BBC Proms | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | date=2013-07-10 | publisher=Classical Source | archive-date=2014-12-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210122836/http://www.classicalsource.com/db_control/db_news.php?id=2497 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[埃萨-佩卡·萨洛宁|埃萨-佩卡·萨洛宁]]和[[爱乐管弦乐团|爱乐管弦乐团]]，<ref name="Slate" />以及[[国家地理_(杂志)|国家地理杂志]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://blogs.slj.com/touchandgo/2011/10/21/review-march-of-the-dinosaurs-for-ios-2/ | title=Review: ‘March of the Dinosaurs’ for iOS | accessdate=August 12, 2013 | author=Grabarek, Daryl | date=2011-10-21 | publisher=School Library Journal | archive-date=2013-10-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017212401/http://blogs.slj.com/touchandgo/2011/10/21/review-march-of-the-dinosaurs-for-ios-2/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>合作。

